        public boolean hasBranches()
        Returns a boolean indicated whether the children of the node are null or not. If both left node and right node are null it will return true and false otherwise.
        Returns:
        boolean indicated whether the node has children
        See Also:
        BinaryNode

      • nextNodeIsNull

        public boolean nextNodeIsNull(java.lang.String key_)
        Returns a boolean indicated whether the next child node according to key_ is null or not. This is useful when the BinaryNodeTree class is looking for a place to store a key.
        Parameters:
        key_ - The key that will indicate whether the next node to compare is the left or right node. To do this, the function will compare the key of the node to key_
        Returns:
        boolean indicated whether the next node that corresponds to the key_ has children or not.
        See Also:
        BinaryNode

      • setNextNode

        public void setNextNode(java.lang.String key_,
               java.lang.String value_)
        Sets the value of the next node in the binary tree with a string and a value.
        Parameters:
        key_ - The key that will indicate whether the node to set is the left or right node. To do this, the function will compare the key of the node to key_
        value_ - The value that will be used to set the value of the next node
        See Also:
        BinaryNode

      • printChild

        public void printChild(int level)
        This function will print the child nodes of the node.
        Parameters:
        level - The level in which the node has been placed in the binary tree. This may be useful when using the printing function, for formatting.
        See Also:
        BinaryNode

      • nextNode

        public BinaryNode nextNode(java.lang.String key_)
        Returns the next node in he binary tree according to a provided key. The provided key will be compared to the node to determine whether the left or the right node should be returned.
        Parameters:
        key_ - The key that will indicate which child node to return
